---
description: Code style for Next.js frontend (TypeScript, React)
globs:
  - "frontend/**/*.{ts,tsx,js,jsx}"
alwaysApply: true
---

- Prefer TypeScript; enable `strict` in `tsconfig.json`.
- Follow ESLint + Prettier; fix on save.
- Use React Server Components by default in `app/`; add `"use client"` only when needed.
- Co-locate components in `frontend/components/` and feature areas; prefer small, pure components.
- Use named exports; avoid default exports except for Next.js pages/routes.
- Avoid `any`; leverage discriminated unions and explicit types.
- Prefer CSS Modules or Tailwind; avoid global CSS except in `app/globals.css`.

